        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can a Bluetti portable power station really run a full-size refrigerator?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes. Larger units like the AC200L pack 2,048 Wh of capacity, which can power a standard home refrigerator for roughly 15–20 hours depending on the fridge's wattage. The AC300, with expansion batteries, can extend that to multiple days. Always check your fridge's running wattage (usually 100–200W) and compare it to the station's rated output.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How long do Bluetti batteries last before they need replacing?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bluetti uses LiFePO4 (LFP) battery chemistry across most of their lineup, which is rated for 3,500+ charge cycles. If you cycle it once daily, that's roughly 10 years of use before the battery degrades to about 80% of its original capacity. Even then, it still works—it just holds slightly less charge.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can I charge a Bluetti power station with solar panels?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Absolutely. Bluetti sells compatible folding solar panels (like the PV120, PV200, and PV350) that connect directly to their stations via MC4 or DC7909 connectors. On a sunny day, a 200W panel can fully recharge a 700Wh unit in about 3–4 hours. The MPPT charge controller built into every Bluetti station optimizes solar input even in less-than-perfect conditions.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
